# Cloudflare Pages headers. Buildless app with STABLE filenames (no content hashes), so a long
# browser TTL shadows new deploys with the cached old modules until it expires — worse here
# because the experience is embedded in a cross-origin <iframe>, so even a parent hard-refresh
# doesn't bust the iframe's cached subresources.
#
# IMPORTANT: a Cloudflare Cache Rule on the skindeepmag.com zone forces a 4h browser TTL on
# everything under /js/, OVERRIDING what this file sets there (root files obeyed _headers; /js/
# files were stuck at max-age=14400 no matter what). So the module graph was MOVED out of /js/
# into /app/ to dodge that rule — see public/app/. If that zone rule is ever set to "Respect
# Existing Headers", the path no longer matters.
#
# Also: Pages combines headers from ALL matching rules (no "most specific wins"), so each file
# must match exactly ONE Cache-Control rule — the patterns below are non-overlapping by extension.

# JS (the /app module graph + the vendored three.min.js) + HTML: always revalidate. Stable
# filenames mean a tiny 304 via ETag when unchanged, and the new file immediately after a deploy.
/*.js
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
/*.html
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate

# Textures (.webp) match no other rule — cache a day; bump/purge in the dashboard on the rare swap.
/*.webp
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400
